description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting new opportunity has arisen for a dynamic, motivated individuals to join the Review and Resettlement Team .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Review and Resettlement Team is newly formed team which will work with patients placed in out of area speciality placement .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role allows you the flexible to maintain good work-life balance includes your choice of work base at any of our KMPT locations across Kent – Dartford, Maidstone or Canterbury with the opportunity to partly work from home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have good experience of working with patients with complex mental health and needs. You will work closely with external providers, CCGs and Social services to facilitate timely discharges from out of area Placement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must possess excellent leadership and communication skills, are able to demonstrate a flexible approach to your work, are self-motivated, innovative, professional and a team player.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAlice SigfridJob titleSenior Clinical NurseEmail addressalice.sigfrid@nhs.netTelephone number07887927135&lt;/p&gt;
